Make Arch linux setup script:
	- Make and install dwm and slstatus, add dwm to display manager
	- Make .dwm folder and autostart script with contents
		> Start feh, clipboard manager, set screen resolution, etc. 
	- Install and configure display manager
	- Clone and build AUR manager
	- Install packages
	- Install font(s), mostly just JetBrainsMonoNerdFont
	- Set cursor size and theme 
	- Set kitty config
	- Set .bashrc config, especially bash prompt

Required packages:
qemu virt-manager flameshot neovim neofetch xclip kitty feh dmenu arandr thunderbird steam xorg-xrdb

From the AUR:
spotify zen-browser-bin vesktop ttf-jetbrains-mono-git


